FBIS3-32382 "drlat025_n_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-025 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Feb 1994 Chile Carabineros Director Comments on Human Rights Report PY0502140494 Santiago Radio Cooperativa Network in Spanish 1000 GMT 5 Feb 94 PY0502140494 Santiago Radio Cooperativa Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] Carabineros Director General Rodolfo Stange has rejected the allegations of an international report in which Chile is listed as one of the countries where human rights are still being violated. Stange refused to comment at length on a recent report on this subject. [Begin recording, in progress] [Stange] ...something else. Furthermore, the foreign minister said yesterday that he was studying and assessing the report in order to make a decision. Therefore, since the Foreign Ministry is already taking care of the matter, anything I could say would be out of place. [Question indistinct] [Stange] In any case I reject these...these groundless charges from a foreign country which does not [changes thought]...which has, let us say, other problems to deal with. [end recording] [passage omitted]
